At 11:51 AM 4/15/2002, David Schwarze wrote:

>I have an opinion on the balance issue.  What exactly was balanced?  Just 
>the short block?  Was the flywheel included?  What about pressure plate?  Fan?
>
>My guess is that the balance probably included the short block and 
>flywheel, and probably didn't include the rest.  Your problem could likely 
>be with "the rest".  If you have lots of time and really want to figure 
>this out, it's possible to narrow it down some.  All rotating parts are 
>suspect.  Start by removing the fan.  Start the engine (briefly!!) and 
>check for the vibration.  If no change, you have just ruled out the fan 
>and alternator.  Next step would be to drop the engine, remove the clutch 
>and pressure plate, reassemble and check for vibration again.  Two engine 
>pulls required, but you will be able to rule out the clutch.  If none of 
>that succeeds, you can either take the engine back to the rebuilder and 
>ask that it be properly balanced, or just live with it.

Sorry, I just remembered that this is a type 1 engine.  Please change "fan" 
to "fan belt".  But the engine pull just got easier.  :-)

-David

